.TH GSURF 1 "2026" "gsurf 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gsurf \- GObject Surf, a minimal modular web browser
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gsurf
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ URI ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gsurf
is a GLib/GObject web browser, a port of the suckless
.B surf
browser. Nearly all of its logic lives in the shared library
.B libgsurf
so other applications can embed it via GObject Introspection. Features that
would be surf
.I patches
are implemented as runtime-loaded
.B .so
modules (tabs, ad blocking, a vim-style modal layer, link hinting, history,
bookmarks, a find bar, an MCP server for AI control, and more).
.PP
Configuration is read from a YAML file and, optionally, a compiled C config.
Vim-style modal navigation is available through the
.B modal
module.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config =\fIPATH\fR
Use the specified YAML config file instead of searching the default locations.
.TP
.BR \-\-c\-config =\fIPATH\fR
Use the specified C config file (compiled and loaded at startup).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-yaml\-config
Skip YAML config loading and use the built-in defaults.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-c\-config
Skip C config compilation and loading.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-modules
Do not load any modules.
.TP
.B \-\-generate\-yaml\-config
Print the default YAML configuration to standard output and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-generate\-c\-config
Print the default C configuration to standard output and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-list\-modules
List the available modules and exit.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-fullscreen
Start in fullscreen mode.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the version (and active backend) and exit.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
With the default configuration, common bindings include
.BR Ctrl+l " (focus the address bar),"
.BR Ctrl+t / Ctrl+w " (new/close tab),"
.BR Ctrl+Tab " (next tab),"
.BR / " (find in page) with " n / N " (next/previous match),"
.BR f " (vim-style link hints), and"
.BR Ctrl+ "+/" Ctrl\- " (zoom)."
The
.B modal
module adds vim-style normal-mode keys
.RB ( h / j / k / l ", " gg / G ", " H / L ", " i ", " Esc ).
See
.B \-\-generate\-yaml\-config
for the full, documented binding set.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/gsurf/config.yaml
Per-user YAML configuration.
.TP
.I ~/.config/gsurf/config.c
Optional per-user C configuration (compiled at startup).
.TP
.I @DATADIR@/gsurf/
System data directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GSURF_MODULE_PATH
Override the directory that modules are loaded from.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR surf (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Zach Podbielniak.
.SH BUGS
